## Data Licensing

The MIT License above applies to the **source code** of RU-PlumeScan
(everything under `src/` and the architectural Markdown documents at the
repository root).

Reference and ingested datasets bundled with this repository (under
`data/`) and Earth Engine Assets published by the project carry their own
licenses inherited from upstream sources. Each Feature in the published
Assets includes `data_license` and `data_attribution` properties; the
canonical mapping is:

| Source / dataset                              | License          | Attribution required |
|-----------------------------------------------|------------------|----------------------|
| OpenStreetMap-derived polygons & points        | ODbL-1.0         | "© OpenStreetMap contributors" |
| Global Power Plant Database (WRI)              | CC-BY-4.0        | "Global Power Plant Database, World Resources Institute" |
| World Database on Protected Areas (WDPA)       | CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0  | "UNEP-WCMC and IUCN, Protected Planet" (non-commercial use) |
| VIIRS DNB monthly composites (NOAA)            | Public domain    | "NOAA / NASA / USGS, VIIRS DNB MONTHLY VCMSLCFG" |
| Researcher-contributed CRITICAL ANCHORS        | Public domain    | "Sizov O. (IPNG RAS), RU-PlumeScan project" |
| TROPOMI / Sentinel-5P L3 (ESA / Copernicus)    | Copernicus       | "Copernicus Sentinel-5P data, processed by ESA / Sentinel Hub" |
| Schuit et al. 2023 plume catalog (Zenodo)      | CC-BY-4.0        | "Schuit et al. 2023, doi:10.5281/zenodo.8087134" |
| UNEP IMEO MARS                                 | CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0  | "UNEP International Methane Emissions Observatory" |
| CAMS Methane Hotspot Explorer (Copernicus)     | Copernicus       | "Copernicus Atmosphere Monitoring Service (CAMS)" |

Catalog products published by the project itself (Plume Event Catalogs,
Persistence Maps, Time Series, Reference Baselines) are released under
**CC-BY-4.0**. Cross-attribution rules: when these products are derived in
part from a non-commercial-only upstream source (WDPA, IMEO MARS), the
non-commercial restriction propagates to the derived product per the
ShareAlike clause; consumers must respect upstream licenses.

Per-Feature license metadata is the canonical source of truth and supersedes
this table when they disagree.
